# Skill: burpsuite-control

Control Burp Suite Professional via AT-SPI (native Swing UI automation) and REST API (scans, configuration). Two complementary layers â€” AT-SPI for UI interaction, REST API for scan automation.

## Installation Location

- Burp JAR: `{{BURPSUITE_DIR}}/burpsuite_pro_v2026.jar`
- Launcher script: `~/.local/bin/burpsuitepro`
- {{BURPSUITE_LICENSE_LINE}}

## Two Control Layers

| Question | Tool | How |
|---|---|---|
| UI interaction (tabs, buttons, checkboxes, dialogs, settings) | **AT-SPI** | Python `gi.repository.Atspi` |
| Scan automation, configuration, issue retrieval | **REST API** | `curl http://127.0.0.1:1337/v0.1/` |
| Custom-rendered elements with no AT-SPI node (e.g. gear icon) | **xdotool** | Coordinate-based click (last resort) |

## Prerequisites

### Java AT-SPI Bridge (CRITICAL)

Java Swing does NOT register with AT-SPI by default. All three JVM flags are **mandatory**:

| Flag | Purpose | Without it |
|---|---|---|
| `-Xbootclasspath/a:/usr/share/java/java-atk-wrapper.jar` | Load ATK wrapper class | `Assistive Technology not found: org.GNOME.Accessibility.AtkWrapper` crash |
| `-Djava.library.path=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/jni` | Find `libatk-wrapper.so` JNI lib | ATK wrapper loads but can't talk to AT-SPI |
| `-Djavax.accessibility.assistive_technologies=org.GNOME.Accessibility.AtkWrapper` | Tell JVM to init accessibility | Swing window invisible to AT-SPI |

**DO NOT use `accessibility.properties` in JDK conf** â€” it causes crashes when combined with `-jar` because the ATK wrapper JAR isn't on the regular classpath. Use the `-D` flag instead.

### Environment Variables (CRITICAL)

| Env var | Value | Without it |
|---|---|---|
| `DISPLAY` | `:0` | `HeadlessException` â€” no GUI |
| `AT_SPI_BUS_ADDRESS` | `unix:path=/run/user/$(id -u)/at-spi/bus_0` | Java doesn't find AT-SPI bus, stays invisible |
| `GTK_MODULES` | `gail:atk-bridge` | ATK bridge not loaded into process |

### System Packages

```
at-spi2-core            # AT-SPI daemon
libatk-wrapper-java     # /usr/share/java/java-atk-wrapper.jar
libatk-wrapper-java-jni # /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/jni/libatk-wrapper.so
gir1.2-atspi-2.0        # Python AT-SPI bindings
```

## Launching Burp Suite

The launcher at `~/.local/bin/burpsuitepro` already includes all AT-SPI flags. Just run:

```bash
burpsuitepro &>/tmp/burp_output.log & disown
```

Wait ~25 seconds for Burp to fully initialize before AT-SPI queries.

### Manual Launch (if launcher is missing)

```bash
DISPLAY=:0 \
AT_SPI_BUS_ADDRESS="unix:path=/run/user/$(id -u)/at-spi/bus_0" \
GTK_MODULES=gail:atk-bridge \
java \
  -Xbootclasspath/a:/usr/share/java/java-atk-wrapper.jar \
  -Djava.library.path=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/jni \
  -Djavax.accessibility.assistive_technologies=org.GNOME.Accessibility.AtkWrapper \
  --add-opens=java.desktop/javax.swing=ALL-UNNAMED \
  --add-opens=java.desktop/javax.accessibility=ALL-UNNAMED \
  --add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED \
  --add-opens=java.base/jdk.internal.org.objectweb.asm=ALL-UNNAMED \
  --add-opens=java.base/jdk.internal.org.objectweb.asm.tree=ALL-UNNAMED \
  --add-opens=java.base/jdk.internal.org.objectweb.asm.Opcodes=ALL-UNNAMED \
  {{BURPSUITE_JAVA_AGENT_FLAGS}}
