## REST API

### Enabling the REST API

The REST API is **not enabled by default**. Enable it via AT-SPI:

```python
# 1. Open Settings (gear icon at top-right, ~x=1345 y=79)
#    No AT-SPI node â€” must use xdotool
subprocess.run(["xdotool", "search", "--name", "Burp Suite", "windowactivate", "--sync"],
               env={"DISPLAY": ":0", "PATH": "/usr/bin"})
time.sleep(0.3)
subprocess.run(["xdotool", "mousemove", "1345", "79", "click", "1"],
               env={"DISPLAY": ":0", "PATH": "/usr/bin"})
time.sleep(2)

# 2. Find Settings window and enable REST API
settings = None
for j in range(burp.get_child_count()):
    f = burp.get_child_at_index(j)
    if f.get_name() == 'Settings':
        settings = f; break

find_by_name(settings, "Service running").get_action_iface().do_action(0)
find_by_name(settings, "Allow access without API key (using this option is not secure)").get_action_iface().do_action(0)
```

### API Reference

Base URL: `http://127.0.0.1:1337/v0.1/`

| Method | Endpoint | Parameters | Response |
|--------|----------|------------|----------|
| `POST` | `/scan` | `{"urls": ["https://target.com"]}` | `201 Created`, `Location: {task_id}` |
| `GET` | `/scan/{task_id}` | `?after=STRING&issue_events=INT` | `200 OK`, `ScanProgress` JSON |
| `PUT` | `/configuration` | `ConfigurationRequest` JSON | `202 Accepted` |
| `GET` | `/issue_definitions` | â€” | `200 OK`, `[IssueDefinition]` |

Interactive docs: `http://127.0.0.1:1337/v0.1/` (HTML page with endpoint table)

### Start a Scan

```bash
# Start scan
TASK_ID=$(curl -s -D- -X POST http://127.0.0.1:1337/v0.1/scan \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"urls":["https://target.com"]}' \
  -o /dev/null 2>&1 | grep -i location | awk '{print $2}' | tr -d '\r')

echo "Scan task ID: $TASK_ID"
```

### Monitor Scan Progress

```bash
curl -s http://127.0.0.1:1337/v0.1/scan/$TASK_ID | python3 -m json.tool
```

